div.font: The local data -- the data produced on site -- is cleaned into atomic examples at the place of generation and at the point of need. This data is then put into a local database server. From here it can be used to train a local deep learning model and can also the data can also be synced with a global database offsite for processing with more specialized hardware. These global models can be retrieved from the global database to be used locally/ updated locally.

div.p: Nemesyst manages database setup, data submission and retrieval. In future we would also like to add automated sharding capabilities.

div.p: Here a back-end framework is used to train from the data stored in the global database. This can be any framework configured in any of their supported ways, e.g. using TensorFlow multi GPU and multi machine single model training. The output models from this are serialised and imported into the database for documentation, selection, and reuse.
